FNH FiveseveN IOM (Individual Officer's Model)

This model is unavailable now, is no longer manufactured, and has been replaced with the FN USG model.  This model is very rare, especially in that this is in mint condition!  Less than 200rds through this firearm!

The Five-seven IOM (Individual Officer Model) was the first model of the Five-seven pistol to be offered to civilian shooters, debuting in 2004.  The IOM was similar in its basic design to the Tactical version, but differed in that it had a MIL-STD-1913 (Picatinny) accessory rail, a serrated slide and trigger guard, and fully adjustable sights.  It also had a magazine safety mechanism incorporated into the design, to prevent the pistol from being fired without a magazine inserted.

Package includes:

title: For Sale/Trade:  Fi model d 380.
postcontent:
this is a fi model d 380. firearms international 
This is the model Colt copied with their Government Model 380. 
really nice gun shoots great never had a problem 
asking 350 obo

this pistol is neither a colt nor a star but a mix of the two designed by star and colt/F.I. for possible manufacture by colt as a 'colt pony'. it got as far as being included in either the 1973 colt catalog but never reach production. 

F.I. ended up manufacturing the pistol between 1973 until 1977 using frames and slides manuractured in the u.s.a. and internals parts imported from star. in 1978 Iver Johnson purchased the rights to this pistol and began manufacturing it using inventory from F.I. and then they manufactured all new parts in middlesex, new jersey and later jacksonville arkansas. iver johnson manufactured this pistol until about 1992.

the F.I. model D and the iver johnson pony are locked breech designs so it is capable of handling any factory 380 acp and hot handloads (within pressures limitations) also

title: For Sale:  AKDAL MKA 1919 SHOTGUN, AR15 TYPE, 12G, BLACK
postcontent:
The Akdal MKA 1919 is a gas operated, semi-automatic shotgun manufactured in Turkey by Ucyildiz Arms.  The MKA 1919 not only resembles the M16 rifle but the control and function are similar.  The MKA 1919 is unlike any other 12 gauge shotgun in the U.S. as it is very light, ergonomic, and magazine fed.

  The MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun uses a conventional gas-operated action which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel.  The return spring is also located around the same support tube which is concealed by an enlarged polymer hand guard.  The MKA 1919 barrel can be very easily removed from the upper receiver.   The upper receiver is manufactured from an aluminum alloy while the lower receiver, pistol grip, and stock are manufactured as one piece from impact resistant polymer.     The MKA 1919 comes with two 5-round metal detachable magazines and 3 internal chokes.  The magazine release button mimics the M16 rifle location.  The manual safety also duplicates the M16 style being located on the left side of the receiver above the pistol grip.  The top of the receiver has a carrying handle and  integral picatinny rail for mounting rear sights, or any optical accessories.  The MKA 1919 12 gauge shotgun is appropriate for all levels of hunting and sporting enthusiasts.  It comes in Black and "BONZ" camo versions and is reasonably priced for our distributors and customers alike.      This shotgun is priced to sell, and it comes with 5 magazines.

============
This complete CMMG AR-15 M4 Upper Assembly features a chrome-moly steel barrel with a WASP Melonite treated bore and exterior. M4 feed ramps ensure reliable feeding and the 5.56x45mm NATO chamber allows the use of both commercial or surplus mil-spec ammunition. 

CMMG's durable Weapons Armament Surface Protection (WASP) Melonite treatment is a unique protective coating applied to the barrel that surface-hardens the metal, extending barrel service life by reducing friction in the bore and lessening bore surface wear. Also referred to as Nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, making for easier cleaning and maintenance. Nitriding converts the steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering from the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore.

title: For Sale/Trade:  fi model d 380.
postcontent:
this pistol is neither a colt nor a star but a mix of the two designed by star and colt/F.I. for possible manufacture by colt as a 'colt pony'. it got as far as being included in either the 1973 colt catalog but never reach production. 

F.I. ended up manufacturing the pistol between 1973 until 1977 using frames and slides manuractured in the u.s.a. and internals parts imported from star. in 1978 Iver Johnson purchased the rights to this pistol and began manufacturing it using inventory from F.I. and then they manufactured all new parts in middlesex, new jersey and later jacksonville arkansas. iver johnson manufactured this pistol until about 1992.

the F.I. model D and the iver johnson pony are locked breech designs so it is capable of handling any factory 380 acp and hot handloads (within pressures limitations) also

title: For Sale/Trade:  2004 Arctic Cat F7 EFI 144inch long track EXT Model
postcontent:
You are looking at a 2004 Arctic Cat F7 EFI Extended 144 long track. The machine is in excellent condition, with only minor scrapes and scratches that you would expect from a 9 year old machine. There are 3900 miles on the machine, and it starts on the second pull every tiime. It needs nothing, and is ready to ride. Many extras and upgrades will be included with the sale. See below:

 2004 Arctic Cat F7 EFI 144in Ext Model
 Polished Tunnel
 Brand New SLP Skis and Carbides
 Brand New Fox Zero Front Shocks
 Brand New Sno Pro Front Springs
 Updated 2005 Seat (Brand New)
 Tank Bag with Pockets and Hard Panels
 Trailerable Cover
 1.5 Inch Paddle Track
 Brand New Woody's Gold Picks
 Brand New Fox Rear Shock
 Low Profile Windshield
 Headlight Covers
 Brand New Belt Installed with Zero Miles
 (2) Extra Drive Belts
 3/4 Gallon Arctic Cat Synthetic 2 stroke oil
 Arctic Cat Handguards

NOTE: This is the longtrack model of the F7 EFI. I have had many phone calls and questions and people don't seem to know what they are. It has a much larger suspension and a 144 inch track. Longtrack sleds are designed for deeper snow and "boondocking" as people call it. I have owned trail sleds before, and after owning a long track, I will NEVER go back to a standard 121 inch. My sled before this one was a 2003 F7 EFI Sno Pro, and this is much more stable on the trails, handles all deep snow with ease, never even thought about being stuck, etc. There is a slight trade off in top speed due to the longer track length, but it won't be noticed because when all of the higher horsepower 121inch sleds are spinning in the snow, you will be history due to increased traction with the longer track. F7 EFI cats are rated at 140HP stock. They are not slow, and are still to this day one of the most coveted sleds on the market. As with cars and other high performance toys, if you can't put the power to the ground, it means nothing. The 144 inch track excels at this, as well as mountains riding in Tug Hill, Cohocton, and other places there is deep snow.

I have never had a single problem with this sled. As a matter of fact, it has been nicknamed "old reliable". When my friends Polaris broke, this didnt. When my friends Yamaha broke, this didnt. When my friends Ski-Doo broke, this didnt. It has never been towed, broken down, or unable to continue the ride. If we had snow, I would jump on it right now and ride to Tug Hill with absolute confidence. That is worth a lot with some of todays snowmobiles.

It is stored inside all year round, as the pictures show. It is also registered for 2013, has been serviced with new plugs, chassis greased, etc. 

I can be reached at 585 322 four two three seven.
